The paper deals with a machine learning problem of multi-task one-class classification, which involves learning the structure of multiple tasks simultaneously. This problem is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
